{{Infobox building | name = Adelbert Fischer House | alternate_names = | building_type = | architectural_style = [[Art Nouveau]] | classification = | location = | address = | location_city = Philadelphia | location_country = United States | est_completion = | topped_out_date = | completion_date = | closing_date = | cost = | height = | architectural = | tip = | antenna_spire = | material = | size = | floor_area = | architect = }} The '''Adelbert Fischer House''' is a home in [[Philadelphia]] designed by architect [[Milton Bennett Medary ]].<ref name=phlarch>{{cite book|last=Gallery|first=John Andrew|title=Philadelphia Architecture|year=2016|publisher=Paul Dry Books}}</ref> It was built in 1909. It is one of only several [[Art Nouveau]] buildings in Philadelphia. It inspired later works by [[Robert Venturi]] and [[Denise Scott]].
