== Temperature ==
=== General === {| class="infobox bordered" style="text-align:center" |- !Yearly max temp !Yearly mean temp !Yearly min temp |- class="mergedrow" |{{convert|21.5|°C|°F|abbr=on}} |{{convert|17.5|°C|°F|abbr=on}} |{{convert|13.5|°C|°F|abbr=on}} |} Its average annual temperature is {{convert|21.5|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|13.5|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. In the coldest month – January, typically the temperature ranges from {{convert|10|to|19|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|4|to|11|C|F}} at night. In the warmest month – August, the typically temperature ranges from {{convert|24|to|33|C|F}} during the day and about {{convert|19|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night.
== Temperature extremes == The highest temperature ever recorded is {{convert|44.0|°C|°F|abbr=on}} on 4 August 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dn.pt/pais/interior/este-sabado-foi-o-dia-mais-quente-de-sempre-em-lisboa-9679437.html|title=G.Coutinho and Tapada weather stations meassure the Lisbon highest temperature record|last=|first=|date=5 August 2018|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> while the coldest temperature recorded is {{convert|-1.2|°C|°F|abbr=on}} on 11 February 1956.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ipma.pt/en/oclima/extremos.clima/ |title=Climate Records |publisher=Instituto Português do Mar e da Atmosfera |accessdate=9 April 2017}}</ref>
{{Weather box |location = Lisbon |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan record high C = 24.1 |Feb record high C = 26.8 |Mar record high C = 30.4 |Apr record high C = 33.2 |May record high C = 37.8 |Jun record high C = 42.0 |Jul record high C = 40.6 |Aug record high C = 44 |Sep record high C = 41.4 |Oct record high C = 34.6 |Nov record high C = 28.3 |Dec record high C = 25.2 |year record high C = 44.0 |Jan record low C = -1.0 |Feb record low C = -1.2 |Mar record low C = 0.2 |Apr record low C = 5.5 |May record low C = 6.8 |Jun record low C = 10.4 |Jul record low C = 14.1 |Aug record low C = 14.7 |Sep record low C = 12.1 |Oct record low C = 9.2 |Nov record low C = 4.3 |Dec record low C = 2.1 |year record low C = -1.2 |source 1 = [[Instituto Português do Mar e da Atmosfera|Instituto de Meteorologia]]<ref name="IPMA"/> |date=August 2014}}
== Precipitation == Lisbon has on average 117 precipitation (including [[drizzle]]) days a year (above 0.1&nbsp;mm), ranging from 2 in July to 15 in January.<ref name="HKO"/> The average annual precipitation is 774&nbsp;mm (30 inches), ranging from 4.2&nbsp;mm (0.16 inch) in July to 127.6&nbsp;mm (5 inch) in November.<ref name="IPMA"/>
{{Weather box |location = Lisbon |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan rain mm = 99.9 |Feb rain mm = 84.9 |Mar rain mm = 53.2 |Apr rain mm = 68.1 |May rain mm = 53.6 |Jun rain mm = 15.9 |Jul rain mm = 4.2 |Aug rain mm = 6.2 |Sep rain mm = 32.9 |Oct rain mm = 100.8 |Nov rain mm = 127.6 |Dec rain mm = 126.7 |year rain mm = 774 |Jan rain days = 15.0 |Feb rain days = 15.0 |Mar rain days = 13.0 |Apr rain days = 12.0 |May rain days = 8.0 |Jun rain days = 5.0 |Jul rain days = 2.0 |Aug rain days = 2.0 |Sep rain days = 6.0 |Oct rain days = 11.0 |Nov rain days = 14.0 |Dec rain days = 14.0 |year rain days = 117.0 |unit rain days = 0.1&nbsp;mm |source 1 = [[Instituto de Meteorologia]],<ref name="IPMA"/> [[Hong Kong Observatory]]<ref name="HKO"/> <small>for data of avg. precipitation days</small> |date=August 2014}}
== Sunshine == [[Sunshine duration]] is 2,806 hours per year, from 142.6 - average 4.6 hours of sunshine per day in December to 353.4 - average 11.4 hours of sunshine per day in July.<ref name="HKO"/> This is the above average value for the southern half of Europe because in this part of the continent, sunshine duration varies from about 2,000 to about 3,000 hours per year. However, this is 70% larger value than in northern half of Europe, where sunshine duration is around 1500 hours per year.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}} In winter Lisbon has about three times more sun duration than in the northern half of Europe.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}} {{Weather box |location = Lisbon |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jand sun = 4.6 |Febd sun = 5.4 |Mard sun = 6.7 |Aprd sun = 7.8 |Mayd sun = 9.4 |Jund sun = 10.1 |Juld sun = 11.4 |Augd sun = 11.1 |Sepd sun = 8.7 |Octd sun = 6.9 |Novd sun = 5.2 |Decd sun = 4.6 |yeard sun = 7.66 |Jan sun = 142.6 |Feb sun = 156.6 |Mar sun = 207.7 |Apr sun = 234.0 |May sun = 291.4 |Jun sun = 303.0 |Jul sun = 353.4 |Aug sun = 344.1 |Sep sun = 261.0 |Oct sun = 213.9 |Nov sun = 156.0 |Dec sun = 142.6 |year sun = 2806.3 |Jan percentsun= 54 |Feb percentsun= 61 |Mar percentsun= 57 |Apr percentsun= 68 |May percentsun= 69 |Jun percentsun= 75 |Jul percentsun= 85 |Aug percentsun= 85 |Sep percentsun= 76 |Oct percentsun= 68 |Nov percentsun= 59 |Dec percentsun= 55 |year percentsun=68 |source 1 = [[Hong Kong Observatory]] (mean daily and monthly sunshine hours),<ref name="HKO">[http://www.weather.gov.hk/wxinfo/climat/world/eng/europe/sp_po/lisbon_e.htm "Climatological Information for Lisbon, Portugal" (1961-1990)] - Hong Kong Observatory</ref> climatemps.com (percent possible sunshine)<ref>[http://www.lisbon.climatemps.com/sunlight.php Sunshine & Daylight Hours in Lisbon, Portugal] - climatemps.com</ref> |date=August 2014}}
== Daylight == Lisbon enjoys one of the most optimal number of hours of daylight in Europe. Days in winter are not as short as in the northern part of the continent, the average hours of daylight in December, January and February is 10.3 hours<ref name="weather2travel"/> (for comparison: [[London]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/united-kingdom/london.php</ref> or [[Moscow]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/russia-europe/moscow.php</ref> or [[Warsaw]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/poland/warsaw.php</ref> - about 8 hours). {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;" |+Average hours of daylight<ref name=weather2travel/><ref>http://www.lisbon.climatemps.com/sunlight.php </ref> |- ! Month ! Jan ! Feb ! Mar ! Apr ! May ! Jun ! Jul ! Aug ! Sep ! Oct ! Nov ! Dec |- ! hours of light | 9.8 | 10.7 | 11.9 | 13.2 | 14.2 | 14.8 | 14.5 | 13.6 | 12.4 | 11.1 | 10 | 9.5 |- ! hours of Twilight/Night | 14.2 | 13.3 | 12.1 | 10.8 | 9.8 | 9.2 | 9.5 | 10.4 | 11.6 | 12.9 | 14 | 14.5 |}
== Sea temperature== Average annual temperature of sea is {{convert|17.5|°C|°F|abbr=on}}. In the coldest month – January, the average sea temperature is {{convert|15|°C|°F|abbr=on}}. In the warmest month – August, the average sea temperature is {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}}.<ref name="weather2travel">{{cite web|url=http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/portugal/lisbon.php|title=Weather2Travel.com: Lisbon Climate Guide}}</ref><ref name="seatemperature.org">[http://www.seatemperature.org/europe/portugal/lisbon-august.htm Lisbon average sea temperature] - seatemperature.org</ref>
